      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Leafs",
        "body": "The silence after another lost season hangs heavy over Toronto - 32-36-14, eighth in the Atlantic, a <strong>streak-snapping seven-game slide</strong> that buried the Leafs 31 points back and clinched their 15th-place seed in the playoff lottery. No miracles this time; the core that promised so much delivered 78 points and frustration, exposed by defensive lapses and a goaltending carousel that leaked goals like a sieve. Auston Matthews carried the load as always, his sniper's touch the lone bright spot amid the wreckage, but even he couldn't mask the systemic rot - too reliant on star power, not enough grit from the bottom six. Now the real work begins: Shanahan's front office faces a pivotal offseason, with coaching whispers swirling around Craig Berube as a reset button and free agents like Mitch Marner staring down UFA status. Draft lottery odds loom large, a high pick their best shot at fresh blood. <strong>Watch the May 8 lottery draw - it could redefine this franchise's next decade.</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated April 29, 2026"
      },
