      "lotl": {
        "label": "What's Going On With the Jays",
        "body": "Trey Yesavage stormed back to the mound like a man possessed, firing 5.1 shutout innings in his 2026 debut to <strong>blank the Red Sox 3-0</strong> and snatch a split from Boston's grasp. The Jays, scraping by at 13-16 and mired in fourth in the AL East, 6.5 games back, needed every bit of that vintage shutdown - four hits, three punchouts, zero walks - to halt the bleeding after Monday's 0-5 thud. Vladimir Guerrero Jr. delivered the clutch two-out knock, plating a run in a rally that scored all three tallies with timely hacks. No major injuries surfaced in the grit, but this crew's trajectory screams salvage job - playoff seed ninth, points minus 1.5, yet that one-game streak feels like oxygen. Yesavage, fresh off 2025 World Series scars, looks like the ace they've craved. <strong>Eric Lauer toes the rubber this afternoon against the Sox at 2:07 ET - win the series, or watch the East gap widen into a chasm.</strong>",
        "updated": "Updated April 29, 2026"
      },
